articles.title: Ancient Ape Skull Suggests Human Origins May Lie in Europe, Not Africa - Business Insider
articles.description: The partial skull of the ape, which is called an Anadoluvius turkae, was found in Cankiri, northern Turkey.
articles.content:
The discovery of an ancient ape skull may challenge the long-held belief that the ancestors of apes and humans came from Africa, a controversial new study says.
